<HL>
   Autodie's Credit Extended
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ADIE
</CO>
<IN>
AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)
</IN>
<LP>
   GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. -- Autodie Corp. said it reached an
agreement in principle to extend the forbearance agreement
covering the Amended Revolving Credit Agreement with an
undisclosed number of banks through Nov. 30, 1990.
   The maker of auto parts said the banks have agreed in
principle to temporarily increase the amount of credit
available to $58 million from $55 million during the
forbearance period.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Autodie said it expects to sign definitive agreements with
the banks in the next few days.
</TEXT>
